<subSubSection id="93E865164033FF87FF4E4868FEAEFA59" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph id="DB4D369D4033FF87FF4E4868FEC1FF42" blockId="2.[151,1437,1878,2015]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,213]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
In the four analyzed species of 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4033FF86FDB94868FD4AF802" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1928" box="[560,675,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Luzarinae">Luzarinae</taxonomicName>
, we found the karyotype with 2n = 11♁ in 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4033FF86FB114868FB09F803" authorityName="Sperber, Rocha, Lopes-Andrade &amp; Mesa" authorityYear="2003" box="[1176,1248,1915,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Izecksohniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puri">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4033FF86FB114868FB09F803" box="[1176,1248,1915,1940]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">I. puri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2n = 12♁ in 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4033FF86FA0F4868FF04F82F" authorityName="Martins &amp; da Silva" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzaridella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susurra">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4033FF86FA0F4868FF04F82F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. susurra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2n = 13♁ in 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4033FF86FE0D488CFE1DF82F" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1993" box="[388,500,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Melanotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4033FF86FE0D488CFE1DF82F" box="[388,500,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 2n = 
<specimenCount id="CDF4FD144033FF86FDEE488CFD71F82E" box="[615,664,1951,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="female">18♀</specimenCount>
in 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4033FF86FD33488CFCEBF82E" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2011" box="[698,770,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzarida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4033FF86FD33488CFCEBF82E" box="[698,770,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="43C92A184033FF86FC99488CFC9CF82E" box="[784,885,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,890,914]" captionTargetBox="[185,1399,243,861]" captionTargetId="figure-42@3.[184,1403,237,867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Habitus and karyotype of Luzarinae species. 1, Luzaridella susurra, 2n=12, XX♀; 2, Luzarida lata, 2n=18, XX♀; 3, Melanotes ornata, 2n=13, X0♁, pair 1 present secondary constriction and satellite (arrow); 4, Izecksohniella puri, 2n=12, XX♀. Photography 1, 2 by Luciano de Pinho Martins, 3 by Marcelo Pereira Ribeiro, 4 Edison Zefa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561430/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Figs 1–4</figureCitation>
). All of them presented X0♁-XX 
<specimenCount id="CDF4FD144033FF86FB6548B3FB12F82C" box="[1260,1275,1952,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
sex-determining system, except 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4033FF86FEE248D0FE37F84B" authorityName="Martins &amp; da Silva" authorityYear="2013" box="[363,478,1987,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzaridella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susurra">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4033FF86FEE248D0FE37F84B" box="[363,478,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">L. susurra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the Neo-XY♁-XX 
<specimenCount id="CDF4FD144033FF86FD7C48D7FCEAF848" box="[757,771,1988,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
; the X (and Neo-X) chromosomes are metacentrics with the same size of the largest bivalents of the karyotype; the Neo-Y chromosome of 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FC744F84FB99FF27" authorityName="Martins &amp; da Silva" authorityYear="2013" box="[1021,1136,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzaridella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susurra">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FC744F84FB99FF27" box="[1021,1136,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">L. susurra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small acrocentric (
<figureCitation id="43C92A184032FF87FAE64F84FF4EFF42" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,897,921]" captionTargetBox="[158,1431,238,874]" captionTargetId="figure-55@4.[157,1431,237,874]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Cells meiosis showing the sex-determining system in two species of Luzarinae. 5, diakinesis/metaphase I of Luzaridella susurra ♁ with Neo-XY sex-detemining system; 6, diplotene of Melanotes ornata♁ with all bivalents containing terminal chiasma, and X univalent." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561432/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="967003264032FF87FF3A4FA8FEF2FF42" box="[179,283,187,213]" captionStart-0="TABLE 1" captionStart-1="TABLE 2" captionStartId-0="5.[151,239,151,175]" captionStartId-1="9.[151,239,487,513]" captionTargetBox-1="[165,2001,563,1660]" captionTargetPageId-1="9" captionText-0="TABLE 1. Diploid chromosome number, sex-detemining system, fundamental number and karyotype form in Phalangopsidae crickets. 2n, diploid number; SS, sex system; FN, fundamental number; Kf, karyotype form; As, asymmetrical karyotype; Sy, symmetrical karyotype; Ir, irregular karyotype; trace (-), no information." captionText-1="TABLE 2. Chromosome morphology and centromeric index of the Phalangopsidae crickets. M = metacentric; SM = submetacentric; A = acrocentric; trace (-) = no information; (*) chromosome morphology according to Guerra, 1986." httpUri-1="http://table.plazi.org/id/8F8D66154038FF8DFF1E4EF4FD1FFDB2" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" tableUuid-1="8F8D66154038FF8DFF1E4EF4FD1FFDB2">Tabs 1–2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="8F8D66154032FF87FF1E4C69FB32FC4D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561430" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4561430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" startId="3.[151,264,890,914]" targetBox="[185,1399,243,861]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="DB4D369D4032FF87FF1E4C69FB32FC4D" blockId="3.[151,1436,890,987]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FF1E4C69FED5FC05" bold="true" box="[151,316,890,914]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">FIGURES 1–4.</emphasis>
Habitus and karyotype of 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FDDB4C69FD5EFC05" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1928" box="[594,695,890,914]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Luzarinae">Luzarinae</taxonomicName>
species. 1, 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FCBB4C69FC15FC05" authorityName="Martins &amp; da Silva" authorityYear="2013" box="[818,1020,890,914]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzaridella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susurra">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FCBB4C69FC15FC05" box="[818,1020,890,914]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Luzaridella susurra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2n=12, XX♀; 2, 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FB354C69FAAFFC05" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2011" box="[1212,1350,890,914]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzarida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FB354C69FAAFFC05" box="[1212,1350,890,914]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Luzarida lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2n=18, XX♀; 3, 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FF734C8DFE59FC21" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1993" box="[250,432,926,950]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Melanotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FF734C8DFE59FC21" box="[250,432,926,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Melanotes ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2n=13, X0♁, pair 1 present secondary constriction and satellite (arrow); 4, 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FB5B4C8DFA7FFC21" authorityName="Sperber, Rocha, Lopes-Andrade &amp; Mesa" authorityYear="2003" box="[1234,1430,926,950]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Izecksohniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puri">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FB5B4C8DFA7FFC21" box="[1234,1430,926,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Izecksohniella puri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2n=12, XX♀. Photography 1, 2 by Luciano de Pinho Martins, 3 by Marcelo Pereira Ribeiro, 4 Edison Zefa.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="DB4D369D4032FF87FF4E4B10FEE4FA8E" blockId="3.[151,1437,1027,1486]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FF4E4B10FE74FB8A" authorityName="Sperber, Rocha, Lopes-Andrade &amp; Mesa" authorityYear="2003" box="[199,413,1027,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Izecksohniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puri">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FF4E4B10FE74FB8A" box="[199,413,1027,1053]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Izecksohniella puri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FE5A4B17FDADFB8A" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1993" box="[467,580,1028,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Melanotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FE5A4B17FDADFB8A" box="[467,580,1028,1053]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed symmetrical karyotypes with all M/SM chromosomes, and FN = 20 and 24, respectively. In 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FE2D4B3BFDFDFBD6" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1993" box="[420,532,1064,1089]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Melanotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FE2D4B3BFDFDFBD6" box="[420,532,1064,1089]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both bivalents of the pair 1 presented chromosomes with secondary constriction and sattellite (
<figureCitation id="43C92A184032FF87FEBC4B58FE90FBF2" box="[309,377,1099,1125]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,890,914]" captionTargetBox="[185,1399,243,861]" captionTargetId="figure-42@3.[184,1403,237,867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Habitus and karyotype of Luzarinae species. 1, Luzaridella susurra, 2n=12, XX♀; 2, Luzarida lata, 2n=18, XX♀; 3, Melanotes ornata, 2n=13, X0♁, pair 1 present secondary constriction and satellite (arrow); 4, Izecksohniella puri, 2n=12, XX♀. Photography 1, 2 by Luciano de Pinho Martins, 3 by Marcelo Pereira Ribeiro, 4 Edison Zefa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, arrow). 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FE564B58FD54FBF2" authorityName="Martins &amp; da Silva" authorityYear="2013" box="[479,701,1099,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzaridella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susurra">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FE564B58FD54FBF2" box="[479,701,1099,1125]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Luzaridella susurra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an irregular karyotype, with FN = 16, composed of two pairs of large submetacentrics (1 and 2), but the pair 1 with CI closer to the limit for an acrocentric chromosome; both twice the size of the pairs 3 (small metacentric), 4 and 5 (small acrocentrics). 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FB8F4B80FB76FB3A" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2011" box="[1030,1183,1171,1197]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzarida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FB8F4B80FB76FB3A" box="[1030,1183,1171,1197]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Luzarida lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presented asymmetric karyotype, with FN = 28, composed of six pairs of M/SM chromosomes, and two pairs of acrocentrics (pairs 7 and 8). In the last two species, acrocentric bivalents are among the smallest chromosomes of the complement (
<figureCitation id="43C92A184032FF87FABA4BC8FA7EFB62" box="[1331,1431,1243,1269]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,890,914]" captionTargetBox="[185,1399,243,861]" captionTargetId="figure-42@3.[184,1403,237,867]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Habitus and karyotype of Luzarinae species. 1, Luzaridella susurra, 2n=12, XX♀; 2, Luzarida lata, 2n=18, XX♀; 3, Melanotes ornata, 2n=13, X0♁, pair 1 present secondary constriction and satellite (arrow); 4, Izecksohniella puri, 2n=12, XX♀. Photography 1, 2 by Luciano de Pinho Martins, 3 by Marcelo Pereira Ribeiro, 4 Edison Zefa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Figs 1–4</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="967003264032FF87FF1E4BECFF16FA8E" box="[151,255,1279,1305]" captionStart-0="TABLE 1" captionStart-1="TABLE 2" captionStartId-0="5.[151,239,151,175]" captionStartId-1="9.[151,239,487,513]" captionTargetBox-1="[165,2001,563,1660]" captionTargetPageId-1="9" captionText-0="TABLE 1. Diploid chromosome number, sex-detemining system, fundamental number and karyotype form in Phalangopsidae crickets. 2n, diploid number; SS, sex system; FN, fundamental number; Kf, karyotype form; As, asymmetrical karyotype; Sy, symmetrical karyotype; Ir, irregular karyotype; trace (-), no information." captionText-1="TABLE 2. Chromosome morphology and centromeric index of the Phalangopsidae crickets. M = metacentric; SM = submetacentric; A = acrocentric; trace (-) = no information; (*) chromosome morphology according to Guerra, 1986." httpUri-1="http://table.plazi.org/id/8F8D66154038FF8DFF1E4EF4FD1FFDB2" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" tableUuid-1="8F8D66154038FF8DFF1E4EF4FD1FFDB2">Tabs 1–2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB4D369D4032FF87FF4E4A30FEAEFA59" blockId="3.[151,1437,1027,1486]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
Meiosis. We did not obtain meiotic divisions in 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FD7B4A37FCD2FAAA" authorityName="Sperber, Rocha, Lopes-Andrade &amp; Mesa" authorityYear="2003" box="[754,827,1316,1341]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Izecksohniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puri">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FD7B4A37FCD2FAAA" box="[754,827,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">I. puri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FCFF4A37FC2BFAAA" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2011" box="[886,962,1315,1341]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzarida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FCFF4A37FC2BFAAA" box="[886,962,1315,1341]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">L. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since all analyzed specimens were adult females; we found metaphases I in 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FDA94A5BFD7AFAF6" authorityName="Martins &amp; da Silva" authorityYear="2013" box="[544,659,1352,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzaridella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susurra">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FDA94A5BFD7AFAF6" box="[544,659,1352,1377]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">L. susurra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a pair of heteromorphic homologues that represent the Neo-XY chromosomes, both connected by a terminal chiasma (
<figureCitation id="43C92A184032FF87FD794A78FCDDFA11" box="[752,820,1387,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,897,921]" captionTargetBox="[158,1431,238,874]" captionTargetId="figure-55@4.[157,1431,237,874]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Cells meiosis showing the sex-determining system in two species of Luzarinae. 5, diakinesis/metaphase I of Luzaridella susurra ♁ with Neo-XY sex-detemining system; 6, diplotene of Melanotes ornata♁ with all bivalents containing terminal chiasma, and X univalent." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561432/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); in 
<taxonomicName id="1CF24D1E4032FF87FCED4A7FFC3DFA12" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1993" box="[868,980,1388,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Melanotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="E986EA8F4032FF87FCED4A7FFC3DFA12" box="[868,980,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we found diplotenes with all metacentric bivalentes (ring-shaped) joined by a terminal chiasma, and the X chromosome differing from bivalentes by its rodshaped (
<figureCitation id="43C92A184032FF87FF7D4AA0FED0FA59" box="[244,313,1459,1486]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,897,921]" captionTargetBox="[158,1431,238,874]" captionTargetId="figure-55@4.[157,1431,237,874]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Cells meiosis showing the sex-determining system in two species of Luzarinae. 5, diakinesis/metaphase I of Luzaridella susurra ♁ with Neo-XY sex-detemining system; 6, diplotene of Melanotes ornata♁ with all bivalents containing terminal chiasma, and X univalent." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561432/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
